Internal Mechanisms
pasted-image.tiff
Self-verification occurs when self-relevant meanings match the standards of the identity.
In other words, when one’s internal view of one’s role matches the social expectations of that role.
In this framework, actions are goal-oriented, as individuals tailor behavior to match identity standards.
Mismatches produce negative emotions, while matches produce positive ones.
